Day 16: Business & Company OSINT

Introduction

Welcome to Day 16 of my 30 Days of OSINT (Open Source Intelligence) Challenge.

Today, I explored Business & Company OSINT, one of the most practical and valuable areas of Open Source Intelligence. Every organization leaves behind a digital footprint through its websites, public documents, career pages, social media, business registrations, news articles, and many other publicly available sources.

The goal of Business & Company OSINT is to collect, analyze, and verify this information ethically to better understand an organization's online presence, infrastructure, operations, and potential security exposure.

One of the biggest lessons from today's learning is:

> Every organization leaves a digital footprint. OSINT helps transform scattered public information into meaningful intelligence through careful analysis and verification.




